cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with optimization techniques for neural networks and analyzes the loss landscape of these networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The use of neural networks and optimization techniques also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of the loss landscape can also be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
